Subject: Re: [T2] fuel line hoses...another question

On Monday, June 14, 2004, at 10:12AM, Nik Wiman <nik(-at-)tfrec.wsu.edu> wrote:

>1.  How do I change the small pieces that go to the fuel injectors?  I can't
>get them off!  They seem attached by a mechanism other than the standard
>clamp.  Are they part of the FI unit?

The hose is near impossible to try and pull off. That's a good thing.

Cut them off with an xacto knife being careful not to cut the soft metal of the barbs underneath. Then slide on new 7mm hose. You can either reuse the metal cup at the end before fitting the hose or use a second hose clamp.

